= SDL_GetSurfaceColorMod =
Use this function to get the additional color value used in blit operations.


== Syntax ==
```c++
int SDL_GetSurfaceColorMod(SDL_Surface* surface,
                           Uint8*       r,
                           Uint8*       g,
                           Uint8*       b)
```

== Function Parameters ==
{|
|'''surface'''
|the surface to query
|-
|'''r'''
|a pointer filled in with the source red color value
|-
|'''g'''
|a pointer filled in with the source green color value
|-
|'''b'''
|a pointer filled in with the source blue color value
|}

== Return Value ==
Returns 0 on success, or -1 if the surface is not valid; call [[SDL_GetError]]() for more information.

